&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We don’t expect you to meet every single requirement listed. What matters most is your motivation, mindset, and ability to learn. If you’re excited about this role and think you could be a great fit, we’d really like to hear from you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong product mindset: focus on problems, outcomes, and impact—not just tickets or tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Daily, hands-on agentic AI - genuinely drives work through an agent (Cursor / Claude Code / Codex), not occasional autocomplete.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;2+ years shipping production iOS in Swift + SwiftUI (UIKit a plus)&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineering fundamentals they can apply, not recite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to work cross platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Swift + SwiftUI (UIKit a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core engineering: SOLID, architectural patterns, reactive concepts (Combine or RxSwift), Unit testing, Dependency injection&lt;/li&gt;
